¶ And the \w third|strong="H7992"\w* \w lot|strong="H1486"\w* came \w up|strong="H5927"\w* for the \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Zebulun|strong="H2074"\w* according to their \w families|strong="H4940"\w*: and the \w border|strong="H1366"\w* of their \w inheritance|strong="H5159"\w* was unto \w Sarid|strong="H8301"\w*:

¶ When they had made an \w end|strong="H3615"\w* of dividing the \w land|strong="H0776"\w* for \w inheritance|strong="H5157"\w* by their \w coasts|strong="H1367"\w*, the \w children|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Israel|strong="H3478"\w* \w gave|strong="H5414"\w* an \w inheritance|strong="H5159"\w* to \w Joshua|strong="H3091"\w* the \w son|strong="H1121"\w* of \w Nun|strong="H5126"\w* \w among|strong="H8432"\w* them:
